      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Streaming with Async Generators"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use the async context manager form of the SDK to stream tokens as they arrive:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n\nasync def stream_llm(prompt: str) -> AsyncIterator[str]:\n    \"\"\"Yield text chunks as they arrive from the model.\"\"\"\n    async with client.messages.stream(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    ) as stream:\n        async for text_chunk in stream.text_stream:\n            yield text_chunk\n\n# Consume the stream\nasync def print_stream(prompt: str) -> None:\n    async for chunk in stream_llm(prompt):\n        print(chunk, end=\"\", flush=True)\n    print()  # final newline\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FastAPI SSE Endpoint from Async Generator"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom fastapi.responses import StreamingResponse\nimport json\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nasync def sse_body(prompt: str):\n    async for chunk in stream_llm(prompt):\n        yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'delta': chunk})}\\n\\n\"\n    yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\"\n\n@app.post(\"/stream\")\nasync def stream_endpoint(body: dict):\n    return StreamingResponse(\n        sse_body(body[\"prompt\"]),\n        media_type=\"text/event-stream\",\n        headers={\"Cache-Control\": \"no-cache\", \"X-Accel-Buffering\": \"no\"},\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Async Timeout and Cancellation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM calls can stall (network partition, model overload). Wrap with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "asyncio.wait_for",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " or use httpx timeouts in the client:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\n\nasync def llm_call_with_timeout(prompt: str, timeout_s: float = 30.0) -> str | None:\n    try:\n        return await asyncio.wait_for(\n            client.messages.create(\n                model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                max_tokens=512,\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n            ),\n            timeout=timeout_s,\n        )\n    except asyncio.TimeoutError:\n        return None  # caller decides whether to retry or fail gracefully\n\n# Alternative: set timeout at the client level (preferred)\nfrom anthropic import AsyncAnthropic\nimport httpx\n\nclient_with_timeout = AsyncAnthropic(\n    http_client=httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=httpx.Timeout(30.0, connect=5.0))\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Running Sync Code from Async Context"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Occasionally you need to call a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "synchronous",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " function (e.g. a CPU-bound parser or a legacy DB driver) without blocking the event loop:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom functools import partial\n\ndef cpu_heavy_parse(text: str) -> dict:\n    # Hypothetical synchronous, CPU-intensive parser\n    import json\n    return json.loads(text)\n\nasync def async_parse(text: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Run a synchronous function in a thread pool to avoid blocking the loop.\"\"\"\n    loop = asyncio.get_running_loop()\n    return await loop.run_in_executor(None, partial(cpu_heavy_parse, text))\n\n# For heavy CPU work use ProcessPoolExecutor instead of the default ThreadPoolExecutor:\nimport concurrent.futures\n\n_process_pool = concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor(max_workers=4)\n\nasync def async_heavy_cpu(data: bytes) -> bytes:\n    loop = asyncio.get_running_loop()\n    return await loop.run_in_executor(_process_pool, process_bytes, data)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Task Groups (Python 3.11+)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Python 3.11 added "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "asyncio.TaskGroup",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", which is safer than "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "asyncio.gather",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": if any task fails, remaining tasks are cancelled automatically and all exceptions are collected in an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ExceptionGroup",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def parallel_with_task_group(prompts: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    results = [None] * len(prompts)\n\n    async with asyncio.TaskGroup() as tg:\n        async def run_one(idx: int, prompt: str):\n            response = await client.messages.create(\n                model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                max_tokens=256,\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n            )\n            results[idx] = response.content[0].text\n\n        for i, prompt in enumerate(prompts):\n            tg.create_task(run_one(i, prompt))\n\n    # TaskGroup exits only when all tasks finish or if one raises\n    return results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mixing sync and async Anthropic clients: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "calling Anthropic() (sync) from an async function blocks the event loop for the full LLM duration. Always use AsyncAnthropic() in async code.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Creating a new client per request: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "each AsyncAnthropic() opens a new connection pool. Create one module-level instance and reuse it.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "asyncio.gather without a semaphore: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "1,000 unbounded concurrent tasks each holding an open HTTP connection will exhaust file descriptors and trigger Anthropic rate limits.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Forgetting await: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "client.messages.create(...) without await returns a coroutine object, not a response. The LLM call never executes. This is a silent bug with no error.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Blocking in an async function: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "time.sleep(), requests.get(), or any sync I/O inside an async def blocks the entire event loop. Use await asyncio.sleep(), httpx.AsyncClient, etc.",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "italic"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Async LLM Code"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing async functions requires "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "pytest-asyncio",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and a way to mock the AsyncAnthropic client without making real network calls:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pyproject.toml\n# [tool.pytest.ini_options]\n# asyncio_mode = \"auto\"  # pytest-asyncio \u2265 0.21\n\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, MagicMock, patch\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_single_llm_call():\n    mock_resp = MagicMock()\n    mock_resp.content = [MagicMock(text=\"Test summary\")]\n\n    with patch(\"app.llm.client.messages.create\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=mock_resp)):\n        result = await single_llm_call(\"Summarise this.\")\n    assert result == \"Test summary\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_parallel_summaries_order_preserved():\n    texts = [\"doc_a\", \"doc_b\", \"doc_c\"]\n    call_count = 0\n\n    async def fake_create(**kwargs):\n        nonlocal call_count\n        call_count += 1\n        prompt = kwargs[\"messages\"][0][\"content\"]\n        mock = MagicMock()\n        mock.content = [MagicMock(text=f\"summary of {prompt.split()[-1]}\")]\n        return mock\n\n    with patch(\"app.llm.client.messages.create\", side_effect=fake_create):\n        results = await parallel_summaries(texts)\n\n    assert call_count == 3\n    assert results[0].startswith(\"summary of doc_a\")\n    assert results[1].startswith(\"summary of doc_b\")\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_semaphore_limits_concurrency():\n    \"\"\"Verify that the semaphore prevents more than N concurrent calls.\"\"\"\n    import asyncio\n\n    concurrent_count = 0\n    peak_concurrent  = 0\n\n    async def fake_create(**kwargs):\n        nonlocal concurrent_count, peak_concurrent\n        concurrent_count += 1\n        peak_concurrent = max(peak_concurrent, concurrent_count)\n        await asyncio.sleep(0.05)  # simulate network latency\n        concurrent_count -= 1\n        mock = MagicMock()\n        mock.content = [MagicMock(text=\"ok\")]\n        return mock\n\n    with patch(\"app.llm.client.messages.create\", side_effect=fake_create),          patch(\"app.llm._sem\", asyncio.Semaphore(3)):\n        await asyncio.gather(*[bounded_llm_call(f\"prompt {i}\") for i in range(12)])\n\n    assert peak_concurrent <= 3\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Async Context Managers and Resource Management"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The AsyncAnthropic streaming API uses an async context manager that holds the HTTP connection open for the duration of the stream. Proper resource cleanup matters:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import contextlib\nfrom anthropic import AsyncAnthropic\n\n@contextlib.asynccontextmanager\nasync def managed_stream(prompt: str, model: str = \"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"):\n    \"\"\"\n    Context manager that guarantees the stream is always closed,\n    even if the caller raises or disconnects mid-stream.\n    \"\"\"\n    client = AsyncAnthropic()\n    async with client.messages.stream(\n        model=model,\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    ) as stream:\n        try:\n            yield stream\n        finally:\n            # httpx closes the connection here; any buffered chunks are discarded\n            pass\n\n# Usage in FastAPI \u2014 connection close from the client side is handled correctly:\nasync def sse_generator(prompt: str):\n    async with managed_stream(prompt) as stream:\n        async for chunk in stream.text_stream:\n            yield f\"data: {json.dumps({'delta': chunk})}\\n\\n\"\n    yield \"data: [DONE]\\n\\n\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Async Retry with Exponential Backoff"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For transient 429/529 errors in async code, implement retry without blocking:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom anthropic import AsyncAnthropic, APIStatusError\n\nclient = AsyncAnthropic()\n\nasync def llm_call_with_retry(prompt: str, max_retries: int = 3) -> str:\n    for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n        try:\n            response = await client.messages.create(\n                model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n                max_tokens=512,\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n            )\n            return response.content[0].text\n        except APIStatusError as exc:\n            if exc.status_code not in (429, 529) or attempt == max_retries:\n                raise\n            delay = 2 ** attempt  # 1s, 2s, 4s\n            await asyncio.sleep(delay)\n    raise RuntimeError(\"unreachable\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The single most impactful optimisation for a GenAI backend is switching from sequential to concurrent LLM calls. asyncio.gather with a semaphore is the correct primitive: it preserves result ordering, handles exceptions cleanly, and keeps throughput within rate limits. Everything else \u2014 timeouts, task groups, run_in_executor \u2014 handles edge cases around that core pattern."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}